                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d325">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">715.1715/178: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Spencer</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-10-08T18:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 8, 1920—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>55. Your October 1, 4 p.m., and Department’s October 4, 7 p.m. Department
                    understands that conferences similar to that suggested <pb facs="0418" n="320"
                        xml:id="pg_320"/> have in the past been held at a point on the boundary near
                    Choluteca. If the opportunity presents itself, suggest discreetly to the
                    President that his conferences with President Chamorro be held there.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
